{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b48d54fe-ebbd-43d5-893e-3bbf498b7b1e","content":"I can help point you in the right direction for analyzing your .NET crash dump. The tools available here are geared toward *collecting* dumps, not analyzing them, but here's how to investigate:\n\n**Common analysis tools:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** – cross-platform, .NET-focused\n   - `clrstack` – managed call stacks\n   - `pe` (print exception) – last exception info\n   - `dumpheap -stat` – heap overview\n\n2. **Visual Studio** – open the `.dmp` file directly (Windows), gives integrated debugging experience\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) – with SOS extension (`!clrstack`, `!pe`, `!threads`)\n\n4. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS) – `dotnet-sos install`, then `plugin load libsosplugin.so`\n\n**Quick start with dotnet-dump:**\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nThen inside the session:\n```\n> clrthreads          # list all managed threads\n> setthread <id>      # switch to faulting thread\n> clrstack            # see managed stack trace\n> pe                  # print the exception\n```\n\nWould you like help installing `dotnet-dump` in this environment and running it against your file, or do you need guidance on a specific analysis tool?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"28e272d8-1310-45d6-a40c-d09d08a67a09","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says:\n\n\"USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps for CoreCLR or NativeAOT, capturing dumps from running .NET processes, setting up dump collection in Docker or Kubernetes, using dotnet-dump collect or createdump.\"\n\n\"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing, or for .NET Framework processes.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze/debug a dump, not collect one. \n\nI can provide direct guidance on analyzing the dump file without relying on that skill.","outputTokens":527,"requestId":"C3C6:27C37:1DE7203:218D86A:6A07C3F0"},"id":"2433bf01-40dd-41d9-b194-df879bb7a38a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:10:22.136Z","parentId":"84c79e80-e8bb-4c33-84f4-c1ea76bf8250"}
